                                <condition key="good">
                                  The manuscript is in a good state of preservation. The leather cover prevents the folios from detaching, even if the sewing is broken.
                                  It presents traces of use, especially on the lower outer corners,
                                  which intensify <locus from="92v" to="101r"/>. Folios present stains of various origins. The ink is smudged on <locus target="#144"/>.
                                  Tears that occurred after the parchment making have been repaired by sewing and with patches, e.g. on <locus target="#31 #78 #96"/>.
                                    A tear on <locus target="#38"/> has not been repaired, and the lower outer corner of the folio has been cut away.
                                  A loss is present on <locus target="#110"/>, perhaps burned. The endbands are missing, and only their tiedowns are preserved.
                                  The sewing broke at many points.
                                  The leather cover is abraded.
                                </condition>
